comment: Love your Trini accent, Phoenix.  I have to agree with others in the comments section.  This wasn't a mutually abusive relationship. Amber is in recordings admitting to physically abusing Johnny, Johnny's body guards witnessed her throwing cans, purses, and other things at Johnny.  There are photos from his body guards of bruises and cigarette burns, and of course there was the incident in which she severed the top of his finger on his right hand (he's a guitarist so losing his finger is a big deal), crushed the bone and he contracted MRSA 3 times.  Amber's sister told her friends that Amber was the abuser and Amber was the one who pushed the sister down the stairs, not Johnny.  There is no real evidence that Johnny abused Amber.  Her "evidence" doesn't hold up to scrutiny; her stories aren't consistent - which is a major red flag.  Johnny may be at fault for not leaving the relationship earlier -- he left her after she pooped in his bed, she just got to court first because she expected him to file - but she is the one who told lies to the public to ruin his reputation which caused him to lose movies.  Frankly, as a victim of abuse myself, I am very angry that an abuser has stepped in the role of spokesperson for victims of abuse.  It is a very common tactic for abusers to step forward ahead of the victim and claim the victim role and that's what Amber did.  She glommed onto the metoo movement and now she speaks about DV when she was the abuser.  That all by itself makes her a con artist.  I don't want to be represented by an abuser.  She has nothing to say about abuse that any real victim of abuse wants to hear.  She is being used by organizations who want a "victim" to speak out, but it's false, phony and insincere to have a female abuser represent female victims.  Shame on the UN and the ACLU for using an abuser as a spokesperson.  Shame, shame, shame on them.

comment:
@Fiora @PureSparkles22 @Lili J 
Hi Guys - Thank you all for watching and taking time to leave feedback ğŸ™‹â€â™€â€ I only read what the cards tell me and I do not insert my personal opinion. I also aim to give a nuanced view over and above what is delivered in the mainstream/social media not for the sake of being different but for the sake of making us think and question why situations occur so we can spot the signs and avoid toxic situations that I myself have fallen victim too often. 

I believe @PureSparkes22 was referring to the deposition tapes and audio recordings where she admits hitting Johnny. In my reading I point out that she got with Johnny to social climb and for her career. I try on my platform to avoid using labels such as "narcissist" where I can. This can often be a point of confusion for viewers who want me to "call a thing, a thing". 

There are also recordings and evidence of Johnny getting physical with Amber. It was on the basis of this evidence that the Sun newspaper in the UK was able to win its defamation case in which they called Johnny a "wife be@ter". 
The being made in this reading, when I said that both of them were at fault, is that they were not suited to each other (which I think we can all agree), they were both abusive to each other (there is proof for this) and their careers would not recover. Also, it was pointing out that Johnny is a sweet soul and was naÃ¯ve when he met Amber. He saw the flags but ignored them at great cost to him. 

Therefore, I wanted the take away from this reading to be, don't avoid the signs and trust your gut instincts. Abuse is not perpetrated just by men but also women. Youâ€™re not just born an abuser but you can be pushed to the point where you do things out of character that you regret but by the time it happens itâ€™s too late. This is meant to be a cautionary tale as opposed to who is right and who is wrongâ€¦..Let's learn from the mistakes of others , avoid toxic situations and be safe. Also, it's my wish that we keep our integrity in calling out situations that are not right to help those who can't help themselves w/out  vilification ğŸ•Šï¸
